  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing LocalStorage Simulation**\n\nI\'m working on simulating a LocalStorage database. I plan to call this `/src/utils/storage.ts`. My key tasks are to get the current state of LocalStorage and, if local, initialize a default seed database. This should provide a rich initial experience for the user.\n\n\n**Populating Seed Data Now**\n\nI\'ve decided to initialize the simulated storage with seed data. I\'m focusing on Indonesian-style guilds for the initial population. Specifically, I\'m defining two guilds, \"EVOS Divine Clone\" and \"Sunda Esports,\" including details like guild names, IDs, leaders, contacts, member lists with roles, and even example message board posts to enrich the user\'s initial experience with the simulated storage.\n\n\n**Defining Guild Database Operations**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of database operations. I\'ve laid out the groundwork by outlining a series of functions: `initDB()`, `getDB()`, `saveDB(db: DBState)`, and functions to add, delete, and update members and posts: `addGuild()`, `addMember()`, `deleteMember()`, `updateMemberRole()`, `addMadingPost()`, `deleteMadingPost()`, and `editMadingPost()`. This should cover all basic interactions. Now I need to tackle the login flow!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the local storage state engine in `/src/utils/storage.ts`. It will initialize our local collections with some rich, high-context Indonesian gaming klan/guild mock-data (like \"EVOS Divine Clone\" and \"Sunda Esports\" with scrim announcement schedules and sample players in varying roles: Ketua, Officer, Member) so that you can immediately click around and see the distinct access permissions of each role without having to manually input everything from scratch."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 950229100
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
