  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing Guild Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now focused on building the `/src/components/GuildDashboard.tsx` component. The current plan includes a header row displaying the guild\'s name, its generated ID with a badge, and the Ketua\'s name. I\'m exploring the most efficient way to structure the layout for this initial header segment.\n\n\n**Adding Invite Link & Profile**\n\nI\'ve incorporated an \"Invite Link\" feature, generating a shareable URL that people can copy. Upon clicking the copy button, a confirmation message appears. I\'m also including the logged-in user\'s profile with real name, FF nickname, and role badge. A key addition is a \"Switch Role Test Feature\" for interactive testing, allowing instant role switching between members for high-fidelity verification.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/GuildDashboard.tsx` dashboard compiler component. It ties together the separate sections, displays active stats, and generates a copyable invite link for recruits. Crucially, it includes an innovative **\"Simulasi Akun Roster\" (Sandbox Switch Account)** dropdown so that you can instantly swap identities among the clan\'s members (e.g., switching from being Captain/Ketua to Officer or standard Member) with one click to observe and test the UI permission rules and role restrictions dynamically."
